# .private — Private-only file manifest
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Files listed here exist on `main` for internal development use
# but must NEVER appear on the `public` branch or in NPM releases.
#
# This file is the SINGLE SOURCE OF TRUTH for private/public separation.
# It is consumed by:
#   1. execution/publish_to_public.py  — filtered merge script
#   2. .agent/scripts/release_gate.py  — pre-release validation
#   3. .githooks/pre-push              — local push safety net
#
# Format: one path per line (relative to repo root), # comments, blank lines OK.
# Glob patterns supported: directives/internal_*.md
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# === Internal directives (development SOPs, not for end users) ===
directives/framework_development.md
directives/template_sync.md
directives/skill_development.md
directives/setup_environment.md

# === Internal tooling (sync/validate between private and public repos) ===
execution/sync_to_template.py
execution/validate_template.py

# === Internal documentation (references private repo structure) ===
docs/implementation_plan.md

# === This manifest itself ===
.private
